black.  A value of 0 will leave the brightness unchanged.  A value of 1 will
render the layer completely white.  Other values are linear multipliers on
the effect (values are clamped between -1 and 1).

render 0 black, 1 unchanged, and all other values as a linear multiplier.

The current WebKit implementation clamps values between -1 (black) and 1
(white) [2].  There is a bug open to change the filter effect spec [3].

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_CANVAS
defines.description: Enable the Canvas renderer.  Default is `true`.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_DOM
defines.description:
Enable the DOM renderer (used as a fallback where Canvas is
    not available).  Default is `true`.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_IMAGE
defines.description:
Enable rendering of ol.layer.Image based layers.  Default
    is `true`.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_NAMED_COLORS
defines.description:
Enable named colors.  Enabling named colors adds about 3KB
    uncompressed / 1.5KB compressed to the final build size.  Default is
    `false`.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_PROJ4JS
defines.description:
Enable integration with the Proj4js library.  Default is
    `true`.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_TILE
defines.description:
Enable rendering of ol.layer.Tile based layers.  Default is
    `true`.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_VECTOR
defines.description:
Enable rendering of ol.layer.Vector based layers.  Default
    is `true`.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_WEBGL
defines.description: Enable the WebGL renderer.  Default is `true`.
